  m_text: 'The proletarians have nothing to loose but their chains. They have a world
    to win.

    The bourgeoisie cannot exist without constantly revolutionizing
    the instruments of production, and thereby the relations of production, and with
    them the whole relations of society. Conservation of the old modes of production
    in unaltered forms, was, on the contrary, the first condition of existence for
    all earlier industrial classes. '
